      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITTLE RAT (1) flew the lids from the middle with an impressive turn of foot, going on to clock 30.38 when a 5 length winner over 525m at this track. Can measure up again. GARNET GLOW (2) used the inside to advantage when a maiden winner two back then drew wider last time and could manage only second, beaten a neck (26.39) at Geelong over 460m. Boxed well here. Will give a sight again. FLIPPER PAIGE (6) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth (30.46) in a Mix 6/7 H at this track. Deserves plenty of respect. TWENTY KNOTS (4) collected a minor prize last start at big odds and must be considered.",
